<h3 id="_export_purchase_history">2.2. Export purchase history</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Use the <strong>Export purchase history</strong> function to create a one-time record of information on the items you sold in your online store so far. YOOCHOOSE will use this information to create reliable recommendations out of the box.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock important">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-important" title="Important"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Only export purchase history once</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Only run the <strong>Export purchase history</strong> function once at the very start of your cooperation with YOOCHOOSE. Providing YOOCHOOSE with the purchase history more than once will result in incorrect recommendations.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Exporting the purchase history:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » Client » Select client » Services » Yoochoose</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Purchase history</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the purchase history period to export.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>gear-wheel icon</strong> to export the data.<br>
→ The data will be transferred to YOOCHOOSE.<br>
<strong><em>Tip:</em></strong> YOOCHOOSE does not import data instantaneously. YOOCHOOSE will let you know when the import is complete.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
