<p>Proceed as described below to retrieve a list of events and clicks associated with YOOCHOOSE.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Retrieving statistics:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » Client » Select client » Services » Yoochoose</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the <strong>Statistics</strong> tab.<br>
→ The statistics are shown in chronological order.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="_relevant_template_variables_and_template_functions">2.4. Relevant template variables and template functions</h3>
<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="_container_yoochoose_recommendations">2.4.1. Container_YOOCHOOSE_Recommendations</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Container_YOOCHOOSE_Recommendations</strong> corresponds to the template <strong>Container_ItemViewCrossSellingItemsList</strong> or <strong>Container_ItemViewCrossSellingItemsList2</strong>. However, it only uses the items that were recommended by YOOCHOOSE.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="_link_crosssellingitem">2.4.2. Link_CrossSellingItem()</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The target of the link corresponds to the template function <strong>Link_Item()</strong>. However, an additional parameter is added here, which identifies the viewed items as cross-selling items after the link was clicked on. That is necessary for the collection of data for YOOCHOOSE, but it can also be used for other applications. The parameter that was transferred is called <strong>from_crossselling</strong> and it has the value <strong>1</strong>.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="_additional_mandatory_parameters_for_the_template_function_link_crosssellingitem">2.4.3. Additional mandatory parameters for the template function Link_CrossSellingItem()</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>These additional mandatory parameters for the template function Link_CrossSellingItem() ensure that categories are transferred correctly. Note that the code may neither contain spaces nor line breaks.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>[Link_CrossSellingItem()_]&amp;yc1=[Request_CategoryId_Level1]&amp;yc2=[Request_CategoryId_Level2]&amp;yc3=[Request_CategoryId_Level3]&amp;yc4=[Request_CategoryId_Level4]&amp;yc5=[Request_CategoryId_Level5]&amp;yc6=[Request_CategoryId_Level6]</strong></p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="_additional_mandatory_parameters_for_the_template_function_link_item">2.4.4. Additional mandatory parameters for the template function Link_Item()</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>These additional mandatory parameters for the template function Link_Item() ensure that categories are transferred correctly. Note that the code may neither contain spaces nor line breaks.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>&#123;&#37;&nbsp;Link_CrossSellingItem($_itemID)&nbsp;&#37;&#125;&amp;yc1=$Request_CategoryId[Level1]&amp;yc2=$Request_CategoryId[Level2]&amp;yc3=$Request_CategoryId[Level3]&amp;yc4=$Request_CategoryId[Level4]&amp;yc5=$Request_CategoryId[Level5]&amp;yc6=Request_CategoryId[Level6]</strong></p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The parameters for <strong>Link_Item()</strong> have to be supplemented in the store layout in all item lists (e.g. ItemViewCategoriesList).</p>
</div>
</div>
